{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":55678,"duration_api_ms":55647,"num_turns":7,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"7a26d75a-6af4-4cb1-b2ad-7c1f87140658","total_cost_usd":0.28941654999999994,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24012,"cache_read_input_tokens":142186,"output_tokens":2429,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":24012,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":6,"outputTokens":2429,"cacheReadInputTokens":142186,"cacheCreationInputTokens":24012,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.281923,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":10,"outputTokens":208,"cacheReadInputTokens":25948,"cacheCreationInputTokens":3079,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.00749355,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All four amendments identify genuine, verified defects in the token usage extraction and logging code. Each fix is small, well-scoped, and improves correctness or observability without risk of regression. I confirmed every claim against the actual source at the referenced line numbers.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-1-240e9722","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified at lines 1299-1310: `.as_u64().map(|v| v as u32)` is used for all three token fields. This silently truncates any value above u32::MAX to a wrong number. The Claude path uses serde's native `Option<u32>` deserialization (confirmed at line 1255), which rejects overflow entirely. `u32::try_from(v).ok()` returns None on overflow, which is consistent and correct. Trivial fix, no downside."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-34d48b79","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified at line 186 (Claude path: `Some(p + c)` where p,c are u32) and line 1312 (Codex path: `Some(i + o)` where i,o are u32). Both are unchecked u32 additions that panic in debug builds and wrap silently in release builds. While token counts exceeding u32::MAX is unlikely today, the fix is a single-character change (`checked_add`) that eliminates a real panic path and a silent data corruption path. No reason not to fix this."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-7f5493dc","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified at lines 1296-1321: `value.get(\"usage\")` on `{\"usage\":null}` returns `Some(Value::Null)`, which passes the `let Some(usage)` guard. All subsequent `.get(\"input_tokens\")` etc. on a Null value return None, so the function returns an all-None TokenCounts and stops the reverse scan. A valid earlier `turn.completed` event with real token counts is never reached. This is a confirmed data-loss bug. The fix (skip lines where usage is not an object with at least one recognized field) is correct and the requested regression test will prevent recurrence."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-23e1a360","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified at lines 240-277: `extract_raw_output` (240), `persist_raw_output` (241), `extract_structured_payload` (248), and contract validation (252-256) all use `?` and can return early before the tracing::info! at line 263. Failed or malformed invocations — precisely the ones where token/cost data is most needed for debugging — produce no trace event. Moving or duplicating the log to fire before line 240 (after metadata finalization at line 238) is the correct fix. The metadata including token_counts is already finalized by that point."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"7a133cdb-483f-4a42-ad5a-85bb1c62a290"}
